00020 MemoryMapItem::MemoryMapItem(QDomNode &memoryMapNode): name_(QString()),
00021 attributes_(), baseAddress_(QString()), baseAddrAttributes_() {
00022 
00023         // parse the attributes
00024         General::parseAttributes(memoryMapNode, attributes_);
00025 
00026         for (int i = 0; i < memoryMapNode.childNodes().count(); ++i) {
00027 
00028                 QDomNode tempNode = memoryMapNode.childNodes().at(i);
00029 
00030                 // get name
00031                 if (tempNode.nodeName() == QString("spirit:name")) {
00032                         name_ = tempNode.childNodes().at(0).nodeValue();
00033                         name_ = General::removeWhiteSpace(name_);
00034                 }
00035 
00036                 else if (tempNode.nodeName() == QString("spirit:displayName")) {
00037                         displayName_ = tempNode.childNodes().at(0).nodeValue();
00038                 }
00039 
00040                 else if (tempNode.nodeName() == QString("spirit:description")) {
00041                         description_ = tempNode.childNodes().at(0).nodeValue();
00042                 }
00043 
00044                 // get addressUnitBits
00045                 else if (tempNode.nodeName() == QString("spirit:baseAddress")) {
00046 
00047                         // get base address
00048                         baseAddress_ = tempNode.childNodes().at(0).nodeValue();
00049 
00050                         // get the base address attributes
00051                         General::parseAttributes(tempNode, baseAddrAttributes_);
00052                 }
00053         }
00054 
00055         // check that mandatory elements were found
00056         if (name_.isNull() ) {
00057                 throw Parse_error(QObject::tr("Mandatory element name missing in "
00058                                 "MemoryMapItem"));
00059         }
00060         return;
00061 }

00089 void MemoryMapItem::write(QXmlStreamWriter& writer) {
00090         // the root element must be called just before calling this function
00091         // otherwise the attributes are printed under the wrong element
00092         General::writeAttributes(writer, attributes_);
00093 
00094         // if mandatory element name is missing
00095         if (name_.isEmpty()) {
00096                 throw Write_error(QObject::tr("Mandatory name missing in "
00097                                 "MemoryMapItem"));
00098         }
00099         else {
00100                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:name", name_);
00101         }
00102 
00103         if (!displayName_.isEmpty()) {
00104                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:displayName", displayName_);
00105         }
00106 
00107         if (!description_.isEmpty()) {
00108                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:description", description_);
00109         }
00110 
00111         // baseAddress is mandatory only in base bank but not in
00112         // banked type bank
00113         if (!baseAddress_.isEmpty()) {
00114                 // start the spirit:baseAddress tag
00115                 writer.writeStartElement("spirit:baseAddress");
00116 
00117                 // write the attributes for the element
00118                 General::writeAttributes(writer, baseAddrAttributes_);
00119 
00120                 // write the value of the element and close the tag
00121                 writer.writeCharacters(baseAddress_);
00122                 writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:baseAddress
00123         }
00124 
00125         // go back to the actual class
00126         return;
00127 }
